The paper deals with properties of graphs related to distances between vertices, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of sequentially distance preserving graphs is closely related to simplicial orderings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the distance preserving property on graphs with a cut vertex, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper constructs a family of non-distance preserving graphs from cycles, which is a topic in structural informatics (cs.SI).
